Gift Motupa of Bidvest Wits scores a goal with a header, challenged by Motjeka Madisha of Sundowns. DURBAN - Mamelodi Sundowns came away with a point against Bidvest Wits following their 1-all draw in their Absa Premiership match at the Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban on Tuesday night. The Brazilians are chasing run away log leaders Kaizer Chiefs, and have a packed schedule in the next few days. A draw means that defending champions Sundowns are nine points behind Kaizer Chiefs. Amakhosi has 34 points after 13 games while Masandawana has 25 points with the same matches played. Wits are 14 points behind log leaders with three less games played.